content: is anything more publicly known about the progression of symptoms experienced by the woman. you mentioned above my recounting of the story's detail were "mostly accurate". can you point out where i was inaccurate? how many months from her encounter with the bat til she noticed symptoms? were they mild for a long time before death or did they attack very quickly? a virus that swells suddenly into a fierce spiraling death attack on its host after long hibernation: this is an unnerving (pun intended) notion. how much concern among the public in australia has there been? have large numbers of people become fearful to the point of avoiding places they used to go? has this shocking virus caused any significant disruptions on lives?
